Cell["\<\
The geometrical problem thus posed is, however, clearly intractable.

And for higher-order partitions one loses the possibility even of graphic \
representation of an even more intractable problem.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.554217719006695*^9, 3.554217814637354*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[""], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5542178826840057`*^9, 3.5542178833234043`*^9}}]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Conclusions", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.554217889406076*^9, 3.554217892132639*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Ray's elegant argument is special to the bisection problem",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". And it works only if the random numbers derive from the flat \
distribution. "
}], "Text",
